data.title: Indiana Knights Templar
data.text:
Jeffery W. Prairie was born on April 4, 1965, in Indianapolis, Indiana to James W. Prairie and Frances F. Prairie. Jeff attended and graduated from Brown County High School in Nashville, Indiana. Jeff has been married for 30 Years to Lady Virginia, with 5 Children and 10 grandchildren. Jeff has been employed in the same position for 40 years. Sir Knight Jeff, started his Masonic journey in 2007. Jeff served as Worship Master at Jubilee 746. Jeff has been High Priest, Illustrious Master, and Commander at Shelby York Rite. Jeff is also a member of The Grotto, Night Masons, OES, York Rite College, Order of the Amaranth, and AMD.

Jon graduated from West Washington High School. He then studied Tool and Die Making at Vincennes University and earned an associate degree. He has been employed at Bedford Machine and Tool for the past 32 years as a Tool and Die maker. Jon is married to Rebecca. They have three childrenJulie (Theo), Jordan (Brittany), and Amber. They have four grandchildrenTaylen, Timothy, Teddy, Harmony.

Masonic History:

Member of Mitchell Lodge #228

Past Master of Rob Morris Lodge #282 and Blue River Lodge #457

Past Commander-in-Chief of George Rogers Clark Valley of Scottish Rite

Dual member of Salem and Bedford York Rite bodies

Dual member of Bedford #42 and New Albany #5 Knights Templar

Member of Salem Order of the Eastern Star #286

Member of Constitutional Elm #471 AMD

Member of Corydon York Rite College #207

Member of the Yeoman of York New Albany #7

Member of Regius Cordis Court #110 Masonic Order of Athelstan

Member of Canterbury Chapel #37 Commemorative Order of St. Thomas of Acon
